{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Decoder-Only Means"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A decoder-only transformer generates text one token at a time by predicting what comes next. Each token can only attend to the tokens that came before it — never to future tokens. This "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "causal masking"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is what makes auto-regressive generation possible: the model's prediction for position "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "t"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is conditioned only on tokens 1 through "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "t−1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", so the same forward pass can compute all positions in parallel during training while remaining auto-regressive at inference."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Left: lower-triangular causal attention mask showing each token attends only to past positions. Center: auto-regressive generation appending one token at a time until [EOS]. Right: GPT architecture (masked attention + FFN blocks, LM head) and model size comparison table."}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A GPT-style model has three parts:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Embedding layer:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " token embedding + learned positional embedding, summed. Unlike BERT's sinusoidal positions, GPT uses learned position vectors."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "N decoder blocks:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " each containing masked multi-head self-attention followed by a feed-forward network. GPT-2+ uses Pre-LayerNorm (LayerNorm applied before each sub-layer, not after), which stabilizes training."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language model head:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " a single linear layer that projects from the hidden dimension to vocabulary size, producing logits over the next token."}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "There is no cross-attention — decoder-only models have no encoder to attend to. Each block's only inter-token communication is the causal self-attention."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pre-Training Objective"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The model is trained to maximize the log-likelihood of each token given its prefix — standard causal language modeling:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{L} = \\sum_{t=1}^{T} \\log P(x_t \\mid x_1, x_2, \\ldots, x_{t-1}; \\theta)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is a completely unsupervised objective — any raw text is a valid training example. The label for each position is simply the next token in the sequence, so no annotation is needed."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text Generation with HuggingFace"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM\nimport torch\n\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"gpt2\")\nmodel = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\"gpt2\")\n\nprompt = \"The cat sat on the\"\ninputs = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n\n# Greedy decoding\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    output_ids = model.generate(\n        **inputs,\n        max_new_tokens=20,\n        do_sample=False,   # greedy\n    )\n\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))\n# \"The cat sat on the floor and watched the rain fall...\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Controlling Generation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Several decoding strategies trade off diversity vs. quality:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strategy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key param"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Behavior"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Greedy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "do_sample=False"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always picks argmax. Deterministic, repetitive."}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Temperature sampling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "temperature=0.7"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Divides logits by T before softmax. Lower T → sharper, higher T → more random."}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Top-k"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "top_k=50"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sample from k highest-probability tokens. Prevents very unlikely words."}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Top-p (nucleus)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "top_p=0.9"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sample from smallest set of tokens covering 90% cumulative probability. Adaptive k."}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Temperature + top-p (nucleus) sampling — common production combo\noutput_ids = model.generate(\n    **inputs,\n    max_new_tokens=100,\n    do_sample=True,\n    temperature=0.8,\n    top_p=0.92,\n    repetition_penalty=1.1,   # penalizes repeating the same n-grams\n)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instruction Fine-Tuning"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pretrained decoder-only models complete text, but they do not follow instructions out of the box. Instruction fine-tuning (InstructGPT, Alpaca, LLaMA-Instruct) formats training data as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "prompt → response pairs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and trains the model to produce the response. This is still standard causal LM training; the loss is computed only on the response tokens (not the prompt), so the model learns to answer rather than just complete."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Inference with an instruct model using its expected chat template\nfrom transformers import pipeline\n\ngenerator = pipeline(\"text-generation\", model=\"meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct\",\n                     device_map=\"auto\", torch_dtype=\"auto\")\n\nmessages = [\n    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a concise technical assistant.\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": \"Explain causal masking in one sentence.\"},\n]\nout = generator(messages, max_new_tokens=80)\nprint(out[0][\"generated_text\"][-1][\"content\"])"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-Only vs. Decoder-Only"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-only (BERT)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only (GPT)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention direction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bidirectional (full context)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Causal (left-to-right only)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can generate text?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes — auto-regressively"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training objective"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Masked LM (predict masked tokens)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Causal LM (predict next token)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classification, NER, embeddings"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chat, completion, code generation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only models have become dominant for both generation and (surprisingly) classification tasks with few-shot prompting. However, for tasks requiring the full context of a fixed input — NER, extractive QA, embedding generation — an encoder-only model with bidirectional attention still has a structural advantage."}]}]}]}}